#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.260"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.260:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.260:0.2"
msgid "26. Abhiññāvagga "
msgstr "26. Insight "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.260:0.3"
msgid "260. Dutiyaājānīyasutta "
msgstr "260. A Thoroughbred (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.260:1.1"
msgid "“Catūhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a fine royal thoroughbred with four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and considered a factor of kingship. "

msgctxt "an4.260:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.260:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, rañño bhadro assājānīyo vaṇṇasampanno ca hoti, balasampanno ca, javasampanno ca, ārohapariṇāhasampanno ca. "
msgstr "It’s when a fine royal thoroughbred is beautiful, strong, fast, and well-proportioned. "

msgctxt "an4.260:1.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "A fine royal thoroughbred with these four factors is worthy of a king. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.260:2.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant with four factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world. "

msgctxt "an4.260:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.260:2.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno ca hoti, balasampanno ca, javasampanno ca, ārohapariṇāhasampanno ca. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is beautiful, strong, fast, and well proportioned. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.260:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant beautiful? "

msgctxt "an4.260:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. "

msgctxt "an4.260:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vaṇṇasampanno hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is beautiful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.260:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu balasampanno hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant strong? "

msgctxt "an4.260:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant lives with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and embracing skillful qualities. They are strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities. "

msgctxt "an4.260:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu balasampanno hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is strong. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.260:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu javasampanno hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant fast? "

msgctxt "an4.260:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "an4.260:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu javasampanno hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is fast. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.252, sc6
msgctxt "an4.260:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ārohapariṇāhasampanno hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant well proportioned? "

msgctxt "an4.260:6.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu lābhī hoti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant receives robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. "

msgctxt "an4.260:6.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ārohapariṇāhasampanno hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is well proportioned. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an4.260:7.1"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant with these four factors … is the supreme field of merit for the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.260:7.2"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

